      antibodies proved. The antibodies in the sera at the analyzed ASCA positive cases
      prove a systemic immune response against Saccharomyces cerevisiae and the authors
      suggest the end of the oral tolerance against the yeast's antigens. The diet
      restriction (elemental diet, total parenteral nutrition, and fecal diversion) may
      ameliorate the status of the patients with Crohn's disease. It is speculated that
      the yeast-free diet as a part of the therapy for the ASCA positive patients can
      be reasonable: moreover the permanent "forbidding" of the yeast can be an
      acceptable alternative in case of getting well.
